                    "company": "CAJAL Advanced Neuroscience Training Programme",
                    "description": "Extracellular electrophysiology is the measurement of cellular electrical signalling, performed with an electrode placed outside the cell. \nIt is the most widely-used technique in Neuroscience, and yet, many electrophysiologists never develop a clear idea of how the acquisition system works. To counter this 'black box' approach, I developed a week-long, in-depth course on the electronics and theory behind data acquisition, covering:\n- A basic electronics refresher\n- The equivalent circuit of electrodes and neurons\n- How amplifiers work, and how to build an instrumentation amplifier. \n- How to build your own acquisition system (a breadboard-based device that detects muscle contraction, and can be built at home with the kit contents and a laptop)",
                    "title": "Course Founder and Director - Extracellular Electrophysiology Acquisition ",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
            ]
